This paper deals with natural language processing and the statistical properties of word meanings, which are relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on the intersection of computer science and linguistics. The paper also uses statistical methods and machine learning techniques, which are relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the process of mental exploration, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
